CommunityCentered Services Embedded Counselors and Liaisons
Meet the Embedded Counselors and Liaisons
As part of an effort to increase partnership with cultural and academicbased communities of students at USC Counseling and Mental Health Services in USC Student Health have designated the following embedded counselors and liaisons for mental health outreach and development of relationships with members of the community
Embedded counselors provide therapy services during their weekly schedules for their populations liaisons work with program leads to develop programs that are responsive to the communityâ€™s needs Both roles focus on community engagement outreach and prevention needs Social justice mental health wellbeing connectedness and resiliency are typically the focus while increasing help seeking behaviors decreasing stigma and increase accessibility
